<h2 class="title"><a href="#" style="color:#D99821;">Frequently Asked Questions </a></h2><br />
<details>
  <summary>
    <h2>What is research?</h2>
  </summary>
  <p>Making novel and significant contributions to our understanding of the world, based on reproducible observations and verifiable results.</p>
</details>
<details>
  <summary>
    <h2>Why do research?</h2>
  </summary>
  <p>The discovery and interpretation of facts, revision of accepted theories or laws in the light of new facts, or practical application of such new or revised theories or laws.</p>
</details>
<details>
  <summary>
    <h2>How can we choose a suitable area for research?</h2>
  </summary>
  <p>
-Read scientific literature.<br/>
-Attend conferences/seminars.<br/>
-Brainstorm ideas with peers.<br/>
-Define focused questions in the research area.<br/>
-Ensure the research is fundable.<br/>
</p>
</details>
<details>
  <summary>
    <h2>What is the research problem?</h2>
  </summary>
  <p>The topic you would like to address, investigate, or study, whether descriptively or experimentally. It is the reason for engaging the research.</p>
</details>
<details>
  <summary>
    <h2>Where to find research problems?</h2>
  </summary>
  <p>Existing Theories, consultations, supervisors, experience, seminars and workshops, conferences, current and future trends, brainstorming, social issues, existing literature.</p>
</details>
<details>
  <summary>
    <h2>What are the characteristics of a good research problem?</h2>
  </summary>
  <p>
-Be novel, new, not already investigated<br/>
-Have benefit, practical value, significance/importance <br/>
-Generate research question(s) <br/>
-Do-able within the time frame and expertise<br/>
</p>
</details>
<details>
  <summary>
    <h2>Why a research question?</h2>
  </summary>
  <p>Help in focus the research by providing a path through the research and writing process. It will also shed light on appropriate research methods.</p>
</details>

</details>
<details>
  <summary>
    <h2>What are the characteristics of a good research question?</h2>
  </summary>
  <p>
-Specific<br/>
-State the topic of the study, i.e. the main idea, refer to the problem. <br/>
-Reflect the intervention in experimental research.<br/> 
-Note the target group of participants. <br/>
-Clearly show the purpose of the study. <br/>
-Be written in focused, specific language.<br/>
</p>
</details>
<details>
  <summary>
    <h2>What is research hypothesis?</h2>
  </summary>
  <p>It is a statement about the relationship between two or more variables. It translates the research question into a prediction of expected outcomes.
</p>
</details>
<details>
  <summary>
    <h2>What is the difference between pure and applied research?</h2>
  </summary>
  <p>Pure research includes discovery of new knowledge; theoretical in nature. While applied research includes central purpose to solve an immediate problem.
</p>
</details>
<details>
  <summary>
    <h2>What is the difference between qualitative and quantitative research?</h2>
  </summary>
  <p>Quantitative research generates numerical data or information that can be converted into numbers. While qualitative research generates non-numerical data, verbal data.
</p>
</details>
